02:16.592 --> 02:30.932
what we've been doing over the last couple of weeks because we know even after discussing what we think scripture says about how we should engage in politics, we still know that there will be some disagreements not only over politics, but over anything in your life.

02:31.053 --> 02:36.981
If you are alive and breathing, it is only a matter of time before you find yourself in a disagreement.

02:37.001 --> 02:40.466
And so we figured it would be good to talk about how to do so

02:40.514 --> 02:44.663
Well, even amongst the church body, we refer to you as church family.

02:44.723 --> 02:45.705
I call you church family.

02:45.985 --> 02:50.274
And if your family is anything like mine, then there are some times where we have disagreements.

02:50.294 --> 02:55.725
There are some times where we don't get along and there are some times where we have to agree to disagree.

02:56.046 --> 02:57.970
So we want to learn how to do that well.

02:58.082 --> 03:01.105
I have a lot of random conversations with my wife.

03:01.185 --> 03:08.991
It's one of the sometimes fun parts and sometimes annoying parts about being married to me, is that she has to hear my processing.

03:09.432 --> 03:15.998
And so recently, I told you we, I get a chance to pass in Missouri City campus, but recently we moved to Missouri City.

03:16.438 --> 03:25.246
And because I love and value my friendship so much, we hired a moving company, because I love my friends too much to help, to ask them to help me move.

03:25.686 --> 03:28.068
You know, especially in July, because you start out

03:28.048 --> 03:49.074
friends you move one time in 110 degree weather and I get a cheap little box of pizza and some water and Gatorade and then our friendship is never the same and so I love them enough that I was not cheap and I paid a moving company to help us move and side note that also means that if you love me and value my friendship with you if you ever move

03:49.922 --> 03:51.045
Don't ask me.

03:51.145 --> 03:53.191
Don't put me in a position to tell you no.

03:53.632 --> 03:55.898
As a matter of fact, just come ask me for a donation.

03:56.038 --> 04:00.530
I will help you start a GoFundMe to raise money for a moving company.

04:00.670 --> 04:03.638
I will pay somebody hourly to be there in my place.

04:03.839 --> 04:06.546
They can even put my name tag on so that you feel like.

04:06.658 --> 04:08.760
I'm there with you and I'm there in spirit.

04:08.780 --> 04:24.538
And so we had this movement company and as we were packing everything, me and my wife were rapping some stuff and we were double rapping some stuff and we're just trying to decide what goes in the truck versus what goes in our cars and some stuff we sat aside because we really don't want that to be broken at all.

04:24.818 --> 04:27.501
And here's what I realized in this process of packing and moving.

04:27.841 --> 04:35.570
It's the first note on your fill in the blanks is that we are wired to care for things that we believe are valuable.

04:37.826 --> 04:42.610
We are wired to care for things that we believe are valuable.

04:44.002 --> 04:46.764
I never necessarily had to be taught that.

04:47.485 --> 04:51.729
I don't know if anybody ever sat me down and said, hey, you want to protect these things because they are valuable.

04:51.749 --> 05:00.056
I think just naturally, I realized the value in things, I realized how much they cost, I realized that maybe if something new, I want to keep it looking that way, you've been there before.

05:00.176 --> 05:06.181
You weren't a car person at all until you paid that much money for a car and then all of a sudden you're a car person.

05:06.201 --> 05:13.988
Now all of a sudden you outside, washing your car, you've never been to the car wash, but now you're hand washing your car outside because it has some type of value to you.

05:13.968 --> 05:19.394
we are wired to care for things that we believe or that we perceive as valuable.

05:19.854 --> 05:21.937
And so this is exactly what happened with my moving company.

05:21.977 --> 05:24.499
I had the stuff set aside that I wanted them to move and put in the truck.

05:24.960 --> 05:28.103
And so they showed up and they started moving things.

05:28.123 --> 05:32.668
So they were getting together, they were wrapping like our TVs and our furniture and all of that stuff.

05:32.868 --> 05:34.390
And then let me tell you what these gentlemen did.

05:34.430 --> 05:39.215
I'm not gonna say their name because I'm not trying to defame their company, but I really should.

05:39.235 --> 05:41.477
Let me tell you what they did.

05:41.517 --> 05:43.940
They came into my bedroom.

05:43.920 --> 05:49.127
everything packed and all of that stuff and they were just rapping the furniture and I asked him, hey, do I need to bring stuff for all this stuff?

05:49.147 --> 05:49.908
No, we'll bring it all.

05:50.449 --> 05:51.290
Mr. Mayor, oh, great.

05:51.670 --> 06:00.022
So they come into my bedroom and they grab my mattress and they pick it up with intentions to wrap it, I'm assuming, and they don't wrap it.

06:00.342 --> 06:09.394
They drag my mattress across the ground and get ready to go take my mattress and put it raw into this dusty truck that they were driving.

06:09.730 --> 06:11.778
And I caught them.

06:12.059 --> 06:16.455
I mean, I stopped them and intervened right before they put it in the truck.

06:16.656 --> 06:18.523
They're like, hey, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, what are you doing?

06:18.824 --> 06:21.554
And they're like, oh, we didn't know that you wanted your mattress wrapped.

06:25.538 --> 06:27.480
I apologize, I didn't make that clear to you.

06:28.201 --> 06:29.102
But here's what happened.

06:29.723 --> 06:36.931
They didn't know, they thought that maybe the mattress was just a cheap mattress and the truth is that if it was my way, I probably would have had a cheap mattress.

06:36.951 --> 06:42.137
But right around the time, my wife was pregnant with my son, who's almost two now, which is crazy.

06:42.338 --> 06:49.426
Right around the time my wife was pregnant with my son, my parents approached and said, hey, it's about time you guys invested in a good mattress.

06:49.474 --> 06:53.639
I said, okay, so I went and looked and I said, not gonna spend his college fun on a mattress though.

06:53.659 --> 06:56.843
And so unfortunately, we'll just be stuck so that he can go to college.

06:56.863 --> 06:59.186
And so my parents did is they bought it for us.

06:59.546 --> 07:02.970
So this mattress is like one of the most prized possessions in my house.

07:03.511 --> 07:06.835
And here they are dragging it across the ground.

07:07.275 --> 07:08.277
But here's what I realized.

07:08.717 --> 07:16.146
They didn't treat my mattress the way that I would treat my mattress because they didn't see my mattress the way that I saw my mattress.

07:16.610 --> 07:18.112
They didn't realize it was a gift.

07:18.132 --> 07:21.497
They didn't realize that it was as expensive as it was.

07:21.958 --> 07:25.223
They apparently didn't realize that I lay my face there every night.

07:25.463 --> 07:28.668
And so more than anything, I just don't think they knew that yet.

07:28.688 --> 07:30.230
They didn't really understand how mattresses work.

07:30.952 --> 07:38.543
And in the middle of that, I started to realize that I think this is kind of the issue that we see in our culture.

07:38.964 --> 07:42.048
And this is kind of the issue that we see in our conversations.

07:42.128 --> 07:45.874
And this is kind of the same issues that we see in our disagreements.

07:45.954 --> 07:54.845
is that, here's your next one of the blank, that we don't treat people God's way because we don't view them God's way.

07:56.347 --> 08:02.435
But if these gentlemen have been thinking, oh, here is where you are going to lay your face every night.

08:03.156 --> 08:07.762
These gentlemen have been thinking, hey, this was a significant investment and this was something that was a gift.

08:07.938 --> 08:09.540
And this is something that you want to protect.

08:09.560 --> 08:13.907
And if this was something that was valuable, then that would have been evident in the way that they treated it.

08:13.927 --> 08:16.851
They would have wrapped it, put it in with care, they would have sat it to the side.

08:17.311 --> 08:18.814
They would have done all of that stuff.

08:19.655 --> 08:33.915
And in the same way that as our culture approaches disagreements, and as you and I approach disagreements, if we viewed people God's way, then we would treat them God's way.

08:33.935 --> 08:36.018
But most oftentimes that doesn't happen.

08:36.130 --> 08:39.395
And as a matter of fact, it is quite the opposite.

08:39.575 --> 08:44.422
Most oftentimes, we end up devaluing people who don't think like us.

08:44.843 --> 08:49.029
We end up devaluing people who don't agree with the things that we agree with.

08:49.489 --> 08:52.854
We end up devaluing people who don't vote the same way that we vote.

08:53.435 --> 08:57.561
We end up devaluing people that don't speak the same languages that we speak.

08:58.082 --> 09:03.570
We end up devaluing people that don't see things in the same way that we see them.

09:03.650 --> 09:10.400
And as a matter of fact, when you go on social media and all of these things, you see this trend continue.

09:10.440 --> 09:15.027
We almost dehumanize people and we group them into these categories.

09:15.347 --> 09:17.651
And then we start to treat them like these caricatures.

09:17.931 --> 09:33.554
And what happens is that because we've grouped people that way and because we think about people that way sometimes in our culture, what begins to happen is we are more and more comfortable with throwing people away saying, hey, if you don't think like that or if you think this way, I can't be friends with you.

09:34.178 --> 09:38.583
If you think this way, then you and I just are not gonna get along because I don't want any community with you.

09:39.304 --> 09:43.689
And if you are gonna be like that, you're insensitive and I just have to get you out of my face.

09:44.650 --> 09:56.905
And we end up throwing people away and saying things to them that maybe we don't mean or maybe we do mean, but again, I think it is all rooted in this idea that maybe we don't see people the way that God sees them.

09:57.806 --> 10:01.170
And I wanna prove to you, it's not just our culture that struggles with this.

10:01.570 --> 10:06.823
I want to prove to you in the same way that I had to do some soul searching and prove to myself that I struggle with this.

10:06.944 --> 10:17.170
I want to prove to you that you and each and every person in this room and under sound of my voice in some way struggles with this idea of devaluing and dehumanizing people.

10:17.314 --> 10:23.263
Let me tell you, it's because you have verbiage and language for people that you have devalued.

10:23.523 --> 10:24.825
Let me tell you what you call them.

10:24.845 --> 10:41.611
When you and I get so frustrated with somebody, and we don't start thinking about them as individuals, we don't start thinking about them as their families, we don't start thinking about them as their hopes and dreams and what God calls them, eventually we get to a place where we are so frustrated with people that we just start calling them those people.

10:45.036 --> 10:46.418
And here's the thing.

10:46.722 --> 11:01.639
The proof that you struggle with this is that for most of us, I'm not gonna say everybody, but for most of us, when I say the phrase, those people, some group of people come to your head.

11:03.361 --> 11:14.674
And the truth is that when you think about those group of people, you're not thinking about their names, their families, what God says about them, how you should treat them,

11:15.554 --> 11:26.028
What you may be thinking about is how different they are from you, how wrong their opinions are, how they might treat you, or how you've been mistreated by them, or how other people have been mistreated by them.

11:26.569 --> 11:39.826
And when we get that phrase, those people, it proves to us that we have a natural tendency to devalue people who don't think like us and who don't agree with all of the things that we agree with.

11:40.514 --> 11:44.563
And as a matter of fact, I think it would be good if we could work on forgiveness.

11:44.843 --> 11:48.191
On the count of three, we're all going to shout who ours is out loud.

11:49.013 --> 11:49.895
I am joking.

11:50.035 --> 11:50.676
Don't you do that.

11:52.220 --> 11:57.551
If you could have solved the look on your faces just from up here, because first of all, let me tell you, nobody looked around.

11:57.692 --> 11:58.834
I'm going to shout them out loud.

12:00.802 --> 12:09.434
And I had that thought just because at the last service, as I said, you know, who do you think about when you hear the phrase, those people?

12:09.634 --> 12:10.936
There was a guy sitting right up here on my right.

12:10.956 --> 12:12.198
He said, you want me to tell you?

12:12.478 --> 12:12.999
No, sir.

12:13.760 --> 12:14.020
No.

12:14.601 --> 12:17.145
I would actually want the opposite of you to tell me.

12:17.425 --> 12:19.288
That's why I said, think to yourself.

12:20.589 --> 12:21.230
God, I leave.

12:21.250 --> 12:22.152
It would have been awkward.

12:22.172 --> 12:26.738
And so the point is, I started thinking, well, God,

12:26.850 --> 12:29.473
How should I treat these people?

12:29.493 --> 12:31.376
How should I see those people?

12:31.416 --> 12:37.964
Because I believe that if I can see them the way that you see them, then I might be able personally to treat them the way that you want me to treat them.

12:38.685 --> 12:44.192
And so I remember going to a passage in Ephesians chapter number two, and you can turn there with me.

12:44.252 --> 12:47.737
Ephesians chapter number two is written by a man named Paul.

12:48.838 --> 12:55.026
And Paul was right into this church that was experiencing a lot of division amongst his ranks.

12:55.522 --> 13:04.516
And Paul opens Ephesians chapter two with a reminder to everybody in this church who is listening, as a matter of fact, I'll just read it to you, it isn't gonna be on the screen.

13:04.837 --> 13:11.327
But Paul reminds us chapter two, verse one, that you were dead in your trespasses and in your sins.

13:13.290 --> 13:23.186
Paul opens Ephesians chapter two with this reminder that you and I, when we weren't believers, we were stuck in a place of hopelessness.

13:24.194 --> 13:27.740
that we could not think the way that God wanted us to think.

13:28.761 --> 13:49.394
That's what it means to be dead in our trespasses, admit that you were a servant to your own pleasure, you were a servant to your own desires, that you were abnormally selfish, and that you would have experienced had you died in that place physically, you would have experienced an eternity without God, and that's called hell.

13:50.114 --> 13:56.864
But Paul reminds everybody, which is a good reminder for us, that it is by grace you have been saved.

13:57.365 --> 13:59.748
And it is no work or merit of your own.

14:00.229 --> 14:02.372
Meaning you didn't earn your salvation.

14:02.512 --> 14:04.075
I didn't earn my salvation.

14:04.295 --> 14:07.540
You didn't wake up one day and decide that you were so good and you know what?

14:07.700 --> 14:08.762
I'm better than this.

14:09.102 --> 14:11.826
It was the grace of God on your life.

14:11.874 --> 14:20.307
through faith in Jesus Christ, that God used the Holy Spirit to bring you into recognition of your own sin and of your own wrongful ways.

14:20.527 --> 14:25.234
And he used that to unite you now with Christ and to give you an eternity in heaven.

14:25.254 --> 14:28.640
Paul reminds us that no man has worked for heaven.

14:28.940 --> 14:31.524
And as a result, he's pretty much saying, humble yourself.

14:32.185 --> 14:37.753
Because if not for God, you may be some of quote unquote those people you were thinking about.

14:38.474 --> 14:40.818
Even if they're wrong and still stuck in their sin.

14:41.058 --> 14:45.893
And so part of my life, hey, all of us have seen and fallen short of the glory of God.

14:45.913 --> 14:51.410
All of us have been saved by grace through faith as of no work to our own.

14:51.554 --> 14:56.279
And then in verse 11, Paul starts doing some work socially in this church.

14:56.299 --> 15:00.064
So you had these two groups that really, really didn't get along with each other.

15:00.564 --> 15:02.687
They were Jewish and Gentiles.

15:03.187 --> 15:05.991
And these people had all types of tensions.

15:06.051 --> 15:14.561
And this tension showed up in the way that they spoke to each other, in the way that they spoke about each other, in the way that they interacted or did not interact with one another.

15:15.702 --> 15:19.186
And this is how they were even interacting in the church.

15:19.554 --> 15:23.646
So you can imagine how they may have treated people outside of the church.

15:24.107 --> 15:33.394
And so they had all of these different tensions and all of these different, it led to different ways of being oppressed and different ways of showing up and all of these things.

15:33.922 --> 15:59.083
And what happened is it gotten so bad that it said that Jewish people had such a disdain for Gentile, for the people who were Gentiles, that if a Jewish person walked through a Gentile land, then when they got back home to Jewish ground, before they walked on to Jewish ground, they would like kick the dust off of their feet because they didn't want like dirty Gentile dust in their like good Jewish land.

15:59.944 --> 16:01.106
This is how bad.

16:01.474 --> 16:04.418
the animosity was between these two groups.

16:05.179 --> 16:21.924
And so Paul is doing some work on the relational part of their church in verses 11 through the end of the chapter and chapter in verses one through nine, he's doing all of this work to remind us that all of us have sinned and are now saved by grace.

16:22.245 --> 16:31.218
And nestled right in the middle, right in the middle of this reminder that you've been saved by grace through faith in Jesus Christ.

16:31.938 --> 16:34.221
and that there's work to do for reconciliation.

16:35.021 --> 16:39.146
He gives us this one verse that I think gives us insight into how God sees them.

16:39.747 --> 16:46.174
And remember, when I say them and those people, that to the Gentiles, Jews would have been those people.

16:47.516 --> 16:53.442
God cannot believe you want me to do, talk to, be friends with, and get to understand those people.

16:53.462 --> 16:56.546
And to the Jews, Gentiles would be those people.

16:57.507 --> 17:00.210
And Paul speaks directly into their situation.

17:01.602 --> 17:04.505
And he says this, Ephesians chapter two, verse 10.

17:05.667 --> 17:10.672
He says, for we are God's workmanship.

17:12.014 --> 17:16.559
Pause right there before we keep going.

17:16.579 --> 17:24.128
Think about that context and think about how powerful that word we is.

17:26.470 --> 17:29.714
That for two groups that felt mutually exclusive,

17:30.434 --> 17:47.263
that for two groups who felt they had nothing in common, that for a group who felt oppressed and mistreated by another group, and they were seen as even dogs in their eyes, that Paul stands flat footed in the middle of just about as divided a group you can get.

17:48.445 --> 17:53.754
And he stands, as he says, we are his workmanship.

17:54.836 --> 17:56.178
And even in his language,

17:56.418 --> 18:00.164
He speaks this new language of unity for them that maybe they had not heard before.

18:00.624 --> 18:05.872
And so let's continue reading this as Ephesians 2 verse 10, it says, for we are His workmanship.

18:05.892 --> 18:07.294
Everybody say that word, workmanship.

18:08.957 --> 18:17.650
Then He gives us some insight created in Christ Jesus for good works, which God prepared beforehand that we should walk in them.

18:17.890 --> 18:27.266
And I think that in this one verse, we get some insight into how God views them, how God views those people and how God views the people in our life.

18:27.286 --> 18:34.198
And I think that that's what I want to spend the next couple of moments talking about, how God views those people.

18:35.100 --> 18:39.448
Number one, I think that we learned that God values every person.

18:40.209 --> 18:43.154
God values every person.

18:43.618 --> 18:47.943
How do you know that even based on this one text, Pastor Xavier, it starts with these three words.

18:48.344 --> 18:50.847
We are his.

18:52.689 --> 19:00.778
Means that every person belongs to God because every person was created in the image of God.

19:01.699 --> 19:04.142
And as a result, that person is valuable.

19:05.244 --> 19:09.048
Let me tell you, when I first read this passage, I said, okay, this must be just for believers.

19:09.068 --> 19:10.610
Because Paul is talking to the church.

19:10.690 --> 19:16.001
So if we are His workmanship, created for good works in Christ Jesus, again, that must mean it's just for believers.

19:16.181 --> 19:24.498
But remember, way back in Genesis, God already established that every person was created in the image of God, even if they're not a Christian.

19:24.898 --> 19:31.567
You know that they're created an image of God and that it is God's Spirit who allows them life because that is what gives us animation.

19:31.627 --> 19:33.329
That is what gives us breath, life.

19:33.610 --> 19:37.054
That is what gives us free will, the ability to think and to reason.

19:37.295 --> 19:38.736
It is the breath of God.

19:38.857 --> 19:43.443
And when God decides to remove that breath from you, you and I will cease to be humans.

19:43.903 --> 19:52.034
And so because everybody is created by God, every person is valuable because every person is created in the image of God.

19:52.995 --> 19:54.898
And so when I look at somebody,

19:55.010 --> 20:05.041
And when I'm having a conversation with somebody in the middle of that conversation, I have to remind myself and say, God, this is a person that you see as valuable.

20:07.264 --> 20:08.745
This is a person that you love.

20:10.628 --> 20:12.330
This is a person that you care about.

20:14.552 --> 20:20.278
This is a person that you thought needed to be on this earth at this time.

20:21.840 --> 20:23.442
Because if not, they would not be here.

20:24.770 --> 20:37.185
And so God, you have given them value because when I look at them, because they are created in your image, when I look at them, they should remind me how good of a God you are.

20:38.547 --> 20:51.122
Regardless of the way that they think, regardless of the way that they act, regardless of the way that they behave, even regardless of the way that they sin and are wrong, God, this is a person that you have created.

20:51.746 --> 20:53.528
And this is a person that's created in your image.

20:53.949 --> 20:57.773
And I want you to think about how your conversations with people would change.

20:58.214 --> 21:01.618
And how the way you see people and how the way I see people would change.

21:01.638 --> 21:04.001
I want you to think about how social media would change.

21:04.522 --> 21:15.455
If before you ever got a chance to type, or before anybody got a chance to type, there was a reminder to just pop up like, as soon as you did, just wanted to remind you, this person is created in the image of God and they are valuable to God.

21:16.977 --> 21:19.580
Let it be sometimes you'd be so mad, upset, you'd be like, get that out of my way.

21:19.681 --> 21:20.882
You, no, I'm joking.

21:23.106 --> 21:25.088
But the point is, how would that change?

21:27.311 --> 21:30.555
As a matter of fact, it would mean that we should treat everybody.

21:30.615 --> 21:32.457
Everybody should get the VIP treatment.

21:33.098 --> 21:34.860
Here's what happens to you and I subconsciously.

21:34.900 --> 21:36.522
You don't do it on purpose.

21:36.542 --> 21:39.526
It's just human nature because we're sinful and selfish.

21:40.447 --> 21:44.933
Naturally, you believe you are the hero of the world's story.

21:44.953 --> 21:49.298
That you are the main character and everybody else in the world is there.

21:49.410 --> 21:53.220
to submit to and to help God's plan for your life.

21:53.581 --> 21:55.646
That your family is the most important family.

21:55.907 --> 21:58.293
Your feelings and my feelings are the most important feelings.

21:58.674 --> 22:03.346
And this is naturally what we think and how we react and how we act.

22:04.258 --> 22:19.793
but I think the Lord is calling us to see the value in every other person and say, God, you are doing something purposeful in their life, in their family, and you created them with value, and as a result, I should treat them that way.

22:20.594 --> 22:33.266
As a matter of fact, Colossians 3.12 calls us, therefore, as God's chosen people, holy and dearly loved, clothe yourselves with compassion, kindness, humility,

22:34.018 --> 22:36.101
gentleness and patience.

22:38.184 --> 22:45.976
As people who have already received being dearly loved, I should clothe myself with these things.

22:45.996 --> 22:48.279
They should overflow out of my life.

22:48.640 --> 22:54.548
In every conversation, people should be able to speak highly of my gentleness.

22:55.950 --> 22:58.354
They should speak highly of my kindness.

22:59.426 --> 23:05.616
But that only happens when I learn to see the person in front of me as somebody that God loves and that God values.

23:06.538 --> 23:08.561
Number one, God values every person, we are his.

23:08.841 --> 23:11.987
Number two, God created everyone uniquely.

23:14.150 --> 23:17.295
That's, we know this because we get this word right there, workmanship.

23:17.315 --> 23:18.898
This is, we are his.

23:19.138 --> 23:26.011
And that word, workmanship in the original language would be the word poema is where we get the English word poem from.

23:26.612 --> 23:28.777
And it means that they are skillfully designed.

23:28.817 --> 23:30.099
That God took time.

23:30.801 --> 23:35.730
That as you look around, it is clear to you and I that we are not mass produced in some type of factory.

23:35.810 --> 23:36.972
that all of us are different.

23:37.293 --> 24:00.434
We have different skin tones, we have different languages, we have different ways of thinking that some of us are introverts and some of us are extroverts and some of us are socially bold and some of us are socially shy and some of us get more offended more quickly than others and all of those things are just different uniquenesses that God designed us with and all of those uniquenesses make us valuable to God.

24:02.338 --> 24:12.522
that when I look at the differences in how we think, when I look at the differences in how we view things, it should remind me of how creative God is.

24:14.246 --> 24:20.882
And if I see the differences and the uniquenesses as valuable, it will change how I approach them.

24:21.954 --> 24:36.689
And it will remind me that in the same way that I have differences with people physically that God has allowed us to experience different things along our life, and those different experiences shape the way we interact with the world around us.

24:37.389 --> 24:38.270
Now, let me be very clear.

24:38.530 --> 24:39.992
They do not shape the truth.

24:40.953 --> 24:43.475
Your experience does not change what is true.

24:43.616 --> 24:46.278
My experience does not change what is true.

24:46.619 --> 24:50.162
The truth is solidified and set by God's Word.

24:50.914 --> 24:55.639
Now everything else in my life though will be shaped by my experiences.

24:56.440 --> 24:57.802
So what does that mean, Pastor Xavier?

24:58.062 --> 25:06.071
It means that when it comes to the scripture and the Bible and how we interact with people, that anything that is not sin is just preference.

25:08.354 --> 25:12.038
Anything that is not sin is just preference.

25:12.638 --> 25:17.624
And I cannot force my preferences on to other people.

25:17.644 --> 25:19.346
Cannot force my opinions

25:19.650 --> 25:20.852
on to other people.

25:22.393 --> 25:34.829
And what happens is we get so frustrated with people who don't see our preferences that, again, we are willing to not speak to them, willing to not invite them places, willing not to get to know them.

25:34.869 --> 25:36.271
We devalue them as people.

25:36.291 --> 25:40.456
And this is what happens in our culture over and over and over and over.

25:40.757 --> 25:46.044
And what we have to do is to learn to see people uniquely.

25:46.084 --> 25:47.986
Now, again,

25:48.066 --> 25:50.149
even when we see sin in people's lives.

25:50.610 --> 25:52.993
Jesus is very clear about how we address that sin.

25:53.334 --> 25:57.080
As a matter of fact, Jesus is preaching and he says, hey, hypocrite, here's what I want you to do.

25:57.881 --> 26:03.329
You shouldn't complain about the speck of dust in your brother's eye when there is a plank in your own.

26:03.610 --> 26:11.762
So what he says is, you should start by removing the plank from your eye and then you can see clearly to get the speck of dust out of your brother's eye.

26:11.842 --> 26:13.604
And let me tell you what we do.

26:13.624 --> 26:17.527
You get online, I get online sometimes, and well, actually, I don't do that, I would get fired.

26:17.788 --> 26:21.391
But I want to get online sometimes, and I want to tell people how crazy they are.

26:21.411 --> 26:22.872
I cannot believe you think like this.

26:23.093 --> 26:24.334
I cannot believe blah, blah, blah, blah.

26:24.514 --> 26:25.795
And I always want to rattle it off.

26:25.815 --> 26:26.636
And you know what I say?

26:26.716 --> 26:30.300
I say, because I'm just so frustrated with how sinful people are.

26:31.941 --> 26:33.783
But I ain't frustrated about the sin in my own life.

26:35.304 --> 26:37.146
I'm just frustrated by their sin.

26:38.587 --> 26:41.330
If you don't get as frustrated with your greed,

26:42.274 --> 26:50.563
As you do with people's online sin, Jesus would say to you, hypocrite, remove the plank from your eye.

26:51.323 --> 26:54.126
I'm not telling you not to be frustrated with sin.

26:54.587 --> 26:59.232
I'm telling you to be frustrated with all sin that it should grieve you.

26:59.572 --> 27:06.519
I know that you have issues with all of these things and how people think and you want to change these things because that's what the Bible says is right.

27:06.779 --> 27:09.362
But you ain't frustrated with the fact that you addicted to pornography.

27:11.266 --> 27:13.789
I wasn't supposed to say that, I'm sorry.

27:13.809 --> 27:14.830
I really wasn't, I didn't write that.

27:16.051 --> 27:20.717
What Jesus would say is don't pick and choose sins to be frustrated with.

27:20.737 --> 27:24.521
That if sin grieves your heart, every sin should grieve your heart.

27:25.442 --> 27:27.925
And so we do not falter away from the truth.

27:28.786 --> 27:32.810
We stand on the truth, but we stand on the truth unilaterally.

27:34.132 --> 27:39.538
We are not, and again, because of that, we are not throwing people away for their sin.

27:40.098 --> 27:43.303
because God did not throw us away for our sin.

27:44.304 --> 27:54.659
And so we learn to do what Jesus invites us to do, which is even when I disagree, I disagree in a way that is full of grace and understanding that everybody is broken.

27:55.219 --> 27:59.826
But full of truth and understanding that God's standard does not change due to our brokenness.

28:00.642 --> 28:13.581
And so God, I say, because this person is unique and because this person is valuable, I want to see them live the way, even if it's sin, I want to see them live the way that you call them to live, but I want to love them to the place that they can live that way.

28:13.962 --> 28:19.410
I want to truthfully tell them, and in a way that's gentle and kind, tell them about their sin.

28:19.938 --> 28:27.733
And again, I cannot stress enough, I am not saying that agreeing to disagree means that we allow people to live sinful lifestyles.

28:27.793 --> 28:28.855
That is not what I'm saying.

28:29.115 --> 28:34.646
I'm saying we stand on the truth, but even in our truth, people leave the conversation feeling valued.

28:36.670 --> 28:38.994
And again, this is not just for strangers.

28:39.170 --> 28:43.595
I want you to imagine how your disagreements will go with your family members, with your children, especially the one.

28:43.836 --> 28:47.840
It seemed like every decision he makes, he makes just to get on your nerves.

28:47.880 --> 28:53.968
It's like, hey, you are trying to do the exact opposite of what I raised you just because I feel like you spend time thinking about this every day.

28:54.148 --> 28:55.470
And we all know those kids in our lives.

28:56.651 --> 29:05.842
But the point is, how would it look if every time I was about to interact and say, okay, God, more than anything, when I leave this conversation, I want this person to live like you want them to live,

29:06.178 --> 29:16.573
But I want them also to feel like they are valued, to feel like they are uniquely created and designed, and to feel like they have a purpose that is rooted in you.

29:18.255 --> 29:19.597
And I think that's the third thing that we see.

29:19.657 --> 29:23.302
God created everyone with purpose.

29:23.322 --> 29:26.747
It says that we were created in Christ Jesus for good works.

29:28.149 --> 29:34.258
It means that if that person is still breathing, and they are, that God has a plan for their life.

29:35.554 --> 29:38.437
Because they weren't just created that idea of workmanship.

29:38.477 --> 29:40.980
When people heard it, they would have thought about like artistry.

29:41.060 --> 29:42.422
They'd have been like, oh my goodness.

29:42.442 --> 29:46.787
So I'm a work of art to be paraded around so everybody can see how good God is in my life.

29:47.868 --> 29:49.430
But God says, hey, you're my workmanship.

29:50.771 --> 29:53.875
But I created you for good works and Christ Jesus.

29:54.455 --> 29:59.601
And I loved you so much that I prepared the work for you before you were even born.

30:00.622 --> 30:01.183
What does that mean?

30:01.563 --> 30:04.146
That means that there are people and you're like, the work is people.

30:04.514 --> 30:05.896
The work is sharing the gospel.

30:06.737 --> 30:11.624
Whatever your purpose is, you can be a business person, full-time ministry, a teacher, a stay-at-home mom.

30:11.865 --> 30:18.775
Whatever your purpose is, your overarching purpose is to tell as many people about Jesus as humanly possible to anyone who will listen.

30:19.997 --> 30:29.291
Because that is our purpose, it means that any person the Lord allows you and how to interact with, if they're a believer, our purpose is to encourage them in Christ.

30:30.312 --> 30:31.634
If they're not a believer,

30:31.714 --> 30:36.806
Our purpose is to love and share the love of Christ with them until they can make a decision for Christ.

30:38.029 --> 30:44.083
And so because that person has a purpose, and I have a purpose as well, when I see them, I say, okay God, what would it look like?

30:44.183 --> 30:45.426
I really want you to think.

30:45.922 --> 30:53.270
If before you had a conversation with somebody or before anybody in our culture had a conversation with somebody, what would it look like to do an affirmation?

30:53.310 --> 30:56.113
God, the person that I'm about to talk with, they are valuable.

30:56.333 --> 30:59.396
They are uniquely designed in you and they have a purpose.

30:59.416 --> 31:04.822
And because you are allowing me to have a conversation with them, it means that they are a part of my purpose.

31:06.183 --> 31:12.370
I get a chance to encourage them and to lead them into a deeper relationship with you or not.

31:12.962 --> 31:19.245
And now, God, I get a chance to steward this person and this moment.

31:19.265 --> 31:24.082
And I say, hey, God, on the end of this, I want us to be closer on the backhand.

31:25.378 --> 31:27.762
Let me tell you how this showed up in my own life about three years ago.

31:27.782 --> 31:31.327
I got here to Sugar Creek and I asked this person if I could share this story, by the way.

31:31.748 --> 31:33.951
I got here to Sugar Creek and I posted something online.

31:33.971 --> 31:36.074
I don't remember what I posted at this point.

31:36.435 --> 31:40.381
But I posted something online and somebody had gotten offended by it because that's what happens online.

31:40.902 --> 31:46.450
And one of the pastors on our staff, another young pastor, pulled me inside and said, hey man, I think that was

31:46.626 --> 31:47.888
I don't think that was a good idea.

31:47.988 --> 31:48.709
I think you're wrong.

31:48.729 --> 31:49.851
I think the opinion is wrong.

31:49.911 --> 31:51.013
I think you shouldn't have posted it.

31:51.274 --> 31:53.217
I think it doesn't make sense and all of that stuff.

31:53.657 --> 31:56.462
And I said, I'll text him back, say, hey, man, thanks for your opinion.

31:56.602 --> 31:58.165
And I put my phone down.

31:58.586 --> 32:05.036
And I just silently reserved that, okay, God, this person is, and this is what I said in my heart.

32:05.096 --> 32:06.358
I'm being transparent with you.

32:06.438 --> 32:07.700
I'm not saying that I was right.

32:07.760 --> 32:08.722
Don't do this.

32:08.834 --> 32:11.697
But I said, okay, God, this person is small-minded.

32:11.717 --> 32:13.499
They don't want to think any differently.

32:13.839 --> 32:16.742
They didn't even approach me and ask questions about my opinion.

32:16.802 --> 32:21.586
They just wanted to throw their opinion at me, didn't ask if I want it or anything like that.

32:21.606 --> 32:23.228
As a result, God, I love this person.

32:23.428 --> 32:24.589
I receive their feedback.

32:24.689 --> 32:25.951
I'll adjust accordingly.

32:26.311 --> 32:27.833
But I don't have to talk to them every day.

32:28.613 --> 32:30.495
I just need to work with them and love them.

32:30.515 --> 32:31.396
Like you said, love them.

32:31.877 --> 32:33.258
But I don't need to interact with them.

32:34.359 --> 32:37.522
And I felt this conviction because I felt like the Lord said,

32:38.594 --> 32:48.430
If this is what you are gonna model, pastor to pastor, then what do you expect people to model?

32:48.450 --> 32:49.311
I said, oh my goodness.

32:49.452 --> 32:57.164
And so I approached him and he and I are both very upfront and we're like, we don't sugarcoat things, we don't do it well.

32:57.184 --> 33:03.314
And so I approached him, I said, hey man, I wanna be friends with you, but not because I want to, but because the Lord told me I had to.

33:03.970 --> 33:06.734
And I know, don't do that, by the way.

33:07.155 --> 33:08.718
I am not suggesting that you do that.

33:08.758 --> 33:10.460
That breaks all the rules of friendships.

33:11.161 --> 33:15.869
And so I said, hey man, the Lord told me that I could not not be your friend.

33:15.949 --> 33:21.818
And so I took time to get to know him and we started building a friendship and all these things.

33:22.059 --> 33:24.523
And I learned so many things about his life.

33:25.424 --> 33:31.794
And I'm telling you, I learned, I can't get into too much of it, but I learned why he thought the way that he thought.

33:32.450 --> 33:45.949
And some people thought he was abrasive and some people thought that he spoke too swiftly, but I understood then an urgency to his life as I understood his background and what he had processed through and the things that he had seen, I understood why he dealt with that level of urgency.

33:46.791 --> 33:52.018
And even now, to this day, there is not a week that goes by that I don't talk to this individual.

33:52.546 --> 33:58.499
that he doesn't call me and check on me, or that I don't call him and check on him, probably not an entire week that goes by in our lives.

33:59.040 --> 34:05.834
And even to this day, let me tell you, there are not many believers in the world who I disagree with more than this human being.

34:08.259 --> 34:13.330
But it does not stop us from being built and being unified in Christ.

34:14.050 --> 34:15.492
Because let me tell you what almost happened.

34:15.512 --> 34:18.276
Here's what happens, and here's what happens in our culture, and I'm running out of time, so we're getting out of here.

34:18.696 --> 34:21.600
We dehumanize people, and this is what almost happened to me.

34:22.021 --> 34:26.066
We dehumanize people when we replace God's label for them with our own.

34:26.847 --> 34:35.679
And so here's what happens, and whenever you see somebody, they have a label on them already, because God put that label there when He created them in His image.

34:36.060 --> 34:37.582
He called them valuable.

34:37.802 --> 34:39.304
This is my friend Fred, by the way.

34:39.825 --> 34:40.466
Say, hey, Fred.

34:41.698 --> 34:49.842
Fred is a dummy not because I'm calling him a name but because you can see anyway You have people in your life like I'm joking

34:50.082 --> 34:54.709
but Fred has a label on him already because God put it there.

34:54.769 --> 34:57.714
And every person you see has a label on them already.

34:57.834 --> 35:00.138
God already called them valuable.

35:00.498 --> 35:07.530
The fact that they are staring you and I in our eyes, the fact that they are a living human being means that God has called them valuable.

35:08.010 --> 35:14.400
It means the fact that they're still living, even if they're not a believer, they get another chance tomorrow to accept Jesus Christ.

35:14.701 --> 35:17.906
It means that God already called them love.

35:18.114 --> 35:19.916
They don't have to receive that label.

35:20.096 --> 35:21.717
They don't have to believe that label.

35:21.897 --> 35:26.301
They don't have to identify as that label, but God created them as that.

35:26.561 --> 35:38.051
When God created them and the fact that they're still alive and breathing means that every person we see is valuable in love and you and I have to learn to see these labels on people when we interact with them.

35:38.071 --> 35:39.052
But let me tell you what we do.

35:39.352 --> 35:41.574
This is what it means to dehumanize somebody.

35:41.594 --> 35:46.579
We see these labels and we say, hey, I'm not gonna treat you like what God says about you.

35:46.799 --> 35:48.100
I'm not gonna treat you like you're valuable.

35:48.080 --> 35:55.427
and like you're loved, I'm gonna treat you like whatever your opinion or whatever my opinion of you is.

35:55.927 --> 35:59.871
And I cover the labels that God said with my own opinion.

36:00.852 --> 36:09.119
Because the truth is, I would never treat somebody that is loved and valuable by God like that, but I treat one of those people like that because one of those people would treat me like that.

36:10.320 --> 36:16.466
And so I devalue who God says they are because of my own personal opinions and biases.

36:16.738 --> 36:19.822
And as a result, I would never throw a child of God away.

36:19.962 --> 36:26.311
I would never throw somebody away and say, I'm not talking to somebody who's valuable and has purpose in Christ and that God wants me to be around.

36:26.331 --> 36:27.573
What do you think I'm not a believer?

36:27.593 --> 36:28.114
I'm a believer.

36:28.234 --> 36:29.295
I value that person.

36:29.576 --> 36:38.268
But then the issue is that when I replace what God says about them with my opinion of them, it allows me to treat them the way that I want to treat them.

36:39.550 --> 36:45.618
And here's the case that I'm making, family, that you and I have to learn to strip away.

36:45.954 --> 36:47.676
The labels that we put on people.

36:48.838 --> 36:50.480
And here's the harder one, Godly.

36:52.103 --> 36:56.529
You and I have to learn to strip away the labels that people put on themselves.

36:58.292 --> 37:01.216
Some people wanna be divisive.

37:01.236 --> 37:03.980
Some people wanna get an interaction out of you.

37:05.141 --> 37:08.086
There are people who hate Christians.

37:09.868 --> 37:14.034
There are people who hate Christian morals and Christian values

37:14.338 --> 37:21.968
There are people who fight daily to make sure that those values are removed as far as they can see from anywhere in your life, even your own personal life.

37:23.831 --> 37:32.603
But let me tell you, their opinion and their label does not change what God already labeled them.

37:33.945 --> 37:41.035
And so regardless of how bad or wrong their opinion is, you and I have to learn to strip off that opinion that they have.

37:42.076 --> 37:43.538
And they say, God, that's just their opinion.

37:44.546 --> 37:45.547
That's just the way they voted.

37:45.587 --> 37:46.528
That's just the way they talk.

37:46.548 --> 37:47.650
That's just the way they see it.

37:47.910 --> 37:48.951
That's just the way they act.

37:49.252 --> 37:51.354
That's just the way they think.

37:51.374 --> 37:52.836
But God, that's not what you said about them.

37:54.078 --> 38:05.512
And God, because I'm a believer and I believe in your word, I believe what you say about this person, more than their opinion, more than their voting, more than their disagreements, more than their agreements.

38:06.833 --> 38:14.162
And as a result, when I can see them, if we see them God's way, we will treat them God's way.

38:15.650 --> 38:23.559
So family, what would it look like for all of us to say, God, I want to do the work of seeing every person?

38:23.579 --> 38:24.660
Do you realize the weight of this?

38:26.462 --> 38:26.762
Amen.

38:28.384 --> 38:38.956
Every person you and I see, every one of them valuable, every one of them loved, every one of them created an image of God.

38:40.518 --> 38:42.540
And what is true about them, we're getting out of here.

38:42.560 --> 38:44.242
What is true about them individually.

38:44.354 --> 38:46.476
It's true about us as a body of believers.

38:49.079 --> 38:54.205
Church, I just wanna read Ephesians chapter two, verse 13 through 15 over you.

38:54.225 --> 39:01.853
I'm not gonna preach it, I'm not gonna explain it a lot, but I want you to hear what Paul said about these people, and I want you to realize that this is the same that's true for us.

39:02.914 --> 39:13.906
Paul is writing, he says, but now in Christ Jesus, you who previously were far away have been brought near by the blood of Christ, for he himself is our peace.

39:14.658 --> 39:35.987
who made both groups into one and broke down the barrier of the dividing wall by abolishing in his flesh the hostility, which is the law composed of commandments expressed in ordinances so that in himself, in Jesus, he might make the two one new person in this way, establishing peace.

39:36.448 --> 39:40.433
Verse 19, so then, I want you to think about this for you and for Sugar Creek.

39:40.854 --> 39:44.178
So then, you are no longer strangers and foreigners.

39:44.706 --> 40:14.098
You are fellow citizens with the saints and are of God's household, having been built on the foundation of the apostles and prophets, Christ Jesus himself being the cornerstone in whom the whole building, being fitted together, is growing into a holy temple in the Lord, in whom you also are being built together into a dwelling of God in the Spirit.

40:15.874 --> 40:19.879
Same family, you and I are being built into God's house.

40:19.899 --> 40:22.443
And God's house is a place of unity.

40:23.925 --> 40:26.488
And God's house is a place of love.

40:28.070 --> 40:30.093
It is not politics that unites our church.

40:30.413 --> 40:31.094
It never will be.

40:31.194 --> 40:33.617
It is not race or ethnicity that unites our church.

40:33.978 --> 40:34.939
It never will be.

40:35.280 --> 40:43.090
We are united by a love for God, a love for God's Word, and a love for the mission of God.

40:44.322 --> 40:48.108
Let me tell you something personally, this is not Bible, this is just personal beliefs.

40:49.189 --> 40:54.137
I have no hope, and I do mean almost no hope, and me and the Lord are working through this.

40:54.637 --> 40:58.583
I have no hope that our country will ever experience unity.

41:00.246 --> 41:03.350
I don't think that unity is found, do we're too different?

41:04.372 --> 41:08.458
Unity is only found in Christ Jesus.

41:09.740 --> 41:13.906
And so I think the world around us will continue to be more and more divided

41:14.114 --> 41:20.863
about everything and come this fall, you may see people more divided than they ever have been in their entire life.

41:20.883 --> 41:22.585
And you know what they're gonna look for?

41:22.625 --> 41:24.728
A place of safety.

41:26.150 --> 41:27.612
They're not gonna find unity in sports.

41:27.632 --> 41:29.154
They're not gonna find unity in education.

41:29.174 --> 41:31.517
They're not gonna find unity in the school that they graduated from.

41:31.737 --> 41:33.299
They're not gonna find unity in politics.

41:33.479 --> 41:37.164
They're not gonna find unity in politics and the people who voted the way that they voted.

41:37.184 --> 41:41.650
But you know the one place in the entire world.

41:42.498 --> 41:49.427
that you should be able to go and find unity no matter what is in the church of Jesus Christ.

41:49.447 --> 41:52.511
And family, that's what we have to be.

41:53.252 --> 41:54.113
It is not an option.

41:55.115 --> 41:57.458
This is not one of those things you and I get to say, well, that's cool.

41:58.058 --> 42:04.186
We have to be unified in this work, in this mission.

42:05.869 --> 42:10.034
On the way out across all campuses, I wanna say this, on the way out across all campuses, we're gonna pray.

42:10.434 --> 42:14.160
But if you are in church right now, you're like, hey, I want to be unified with people.

42:14.281 --> 42:15.423
I want to get to know people.

42:15.783 --> 42:17.086
I want to be in community.

42:17.166 --> 42:19.009
And you do not have community around you.

42:19.029 --> 42:23.296
Then at every campus, as soon as you leave out, we have that Connect Group Expo out there.

42:23.597 --> 42:30.829
That's intentional so that you can say, hey, here's how I get to know people and have genuine conversations and genuine connections.

42:31.290 --> 42:33.434
You may not get along with everybody in there.

42:33.474 --> 42:35.858
As a matter of fact, I don't want you to

42:36.578 --> 42:39.362
I don't even get along with everybody on our pastoral staff.

42:39.523 --> 42:41.366
I don't think like everybody.

42:42.027 --> 42:43.910
But the Lord uses all of our differences.

42:44.891 --> 42:49.398
And we are being built together into a dwelling for God.

42:50.360 --> 42:53.585
His inhabitants here on the earth.

42:53.605 --> 42:55.248
Let's pray.

42:55.268 --> 43:04.402
Father, thank you so much for the fact that you didn't build us to all think, act, behave, and experience the same things.

43:04.738 --> 43:12.075
God, it is in those uniquenesses that we find a way to glorify your name.

43:13.639 --> 43:17.568
God, your scripture reminds us that Jesus tore down all the dividing walls.

43:18.329 --> 43:22.098
And so what we're asking God is that we wouldn't do the work of building them back up.

43:22.562 --> 43:39.224
that we wouldn't separate ourselves and do the work of building them back up based on some way we vote or some way we think or even the way we behave God that we pray that you would allow us to be unified in the truth of your word and in the truth of your gospel because the truth is God that political agendas will change.

43:39.284 --> 43:52.402
The truth is the educational change, the truth that voting preferences will change, the truth God is that everything around us at some point will change but the one thing that never will is this word that you have given to us.

43:53.346 --> 43:55.817
and for that stability we are grateful.

43:56.339 --> 44:00.538
So help us define unity in your word, unity in peace and Christ Jesus and in nothing else.

44:01.000 --> 44:02.025
It's in Jesus' name we pray.

44:02.366 --> 44:03.250
Everybody together say it.

